==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tergiversate
<hw>Ter"gi*ver*sate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>tergiversatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>tergiversari</ets> to turn one's
back, to shift; <ets>tergum</ets> back + <ets>versare</ets>, freq. of
<ets>vertere</ets> to turn. See <er>Verse</er>.]</ety> <def>To shift; to
practice evasion; to use subterfuges; to shuffle.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Bailey.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tergiversation</ent>⟦br⟧
